snippet.textDisplay: David, It’s really fascinating to hear an advanced musician play such a large number of different styles and see where your strengths are. For instance, the SLAPs are super tight and well put together; articulate and punctuated. But the Victor Wooten part, which was using a different technique, seemed a little less tight. It’s not a judgement on your ability to play, but rather just very cool to see that even a pro musician has strengths and weaknesses, because it’s impossible to perfect art :)
